                     * copyright 1997 Ed Blackman *
                     *                            *
                     ******************************

A Rexx script that scans text files for URLs, creating URL objects in a
folder on your desktop.

*************************************************************************

Requirements
============

- OS/2 Warp 3 or Warp 4
    - use under Warp 3 additionally requires WebExplorer to be installed
- Rexx support installed

*************************************************************************

Setup
=====

Run install.cmd and answer the questions asked.

Copy urlget.cmd to a directory on your PATH.

Setup news, mail, etc, programs to be able to call urlget with the name
of the file containing the URL you want to get, or call urlget manually
from the command line.

If you wish to modify installation parameters or uninstall URLGet, run
install.cmd again.

*************************************************************************

